&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vacancy: &lt;/strong&gt;Clinical Charge, Nurse Band 6&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;The Acute Inpatient Services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week:&lt;/strong&gt; 37.5 hours&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Type&lt;/strong&gt;: Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We do more than empower nurses – we inspire them!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you dynamic, enthusiastic and an excellent communicator?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oxleas NHS Foundation Trust is seeking to recruit Clinical Charge Nurses for its Acute In-patient Services which are located in the Boroughs of Bromley, Bexley and Greenwich.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oxleas staff are locally and nationally recognised for the excellent work they do. Working with Oxleas, gives you the opportunity to work with individuals with mental health problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be part of a multi-disciplinary team involved in the delivery of care and therapy for our service users in many unique ways. Obviously, you need to be incredibly passionate about delivering care, as well as keen to be part of a team which will enable you to develop and build on your own psychiatric skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A shift rota system operates, including weekends and night work. Staff induction, in-house training, regular supervision and personal development reviews are mandatory.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A pension scheme is available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Emma Hopkins or Naidoo Armoordon, Modern Matron Woodlands Unit on 02038895176 .This post is not open to applicants from outside the EEA. This is due to the large number of applications we expect to receive, and as such is unlikely to satisfy the requirements of Work Permits UK. Please also note that for some occupations we receive a high amount of applications and where this is evident the post will be closed and we will put a limit on the number of applications that we are able to receive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you do not hear anything within 4 weeks of the closing date, please assume you have not been short listed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Emma Hopkins Job title Ward manager                                                           Email address emma.hopkins1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number02038895031&lt;/p&gt;
